Emma Elekwa, Onitsha  A Police in Anambra State said they have rescued three toddlers  from two women suspected to be child traffickers in Nkpor, Idemili North Local Government Area of the state. Police spokesperson, Haruna Mohammed, who confirmed this while parading the suspects in Awka, the state capital, said the suspects Chisom Ani, 28, and Afamefuna Udodili, 32, were arrested by detectives following intelligence report.  He said, “Preliminary investigation by police detectives attached to Otuocha Division revealed that the two children were allegedly stolen from Enugu Aguleri in Anambra East Local Government Area by one Ani Chisom, ‘f’, aged 28 years of Amuri in Nkanu-East Local Government Area of Enugu State and Afamefuna Udodili,  ‘f, aged 32 years of Orodo in Mbaitolu Local Government Area of Imo State respectively. “Following the public announcement by the Command on the 22/11/2019, parents of the two kids from Enugu Aguleri came and identified their children. “They also revealed their names as Confidence Ejike, ‘f’, aged 5 years and Blessing Ejike, ‘f’. aged 7 months old respectively.” Mohammed said the children have since reunited with their parents, adding that the suspects would be charged after investigations have been concluded. “Commissioner of Police John Abang urges parents and guardians to monitor their children and caution them against following strangers. “The CP further enjoins the public to report any suspicious persons to the nearest police station or call police emergency number 07039194332 for prompt action,” he added.